rComments: Very kind man however marks harshly if opinions do not match his own. Classes can be boring, and sometimes gets sidetracked.

Not entirely helpful and likes to stick to the 'old chalkboard way of teaching'. Really cares about things being memorized and considers that to be a huge part of learning a language. Very kind man, but classes tend to become tedious and sometimes boring.
One of the best Prof's at U of T - he is nice, helpful and fun. The class was ok but he made it a lot more enjoyable. Overall, he is super.
Borje has a very enthousiastic approach to the class and loves to teach.  However, he likes facts a lot and does not take to opinions well if they do not match his own.

hes the kindest man at u of t, sooo helpful and jsut good hearted, really relates to his students...he tries as best as he can since theres not much to finnish cinema...you have to learn at your own level.

An extremely kind man who obviously loves what he does. Understanding of film is somewhat lacking, but he blessedly admitted to it & allowed students to work at the analytic level they found most comfortable. A great intro to Finnish cinema.
Wonderful professor! His classes were actually fun. Helpful & kind prof.
